00w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Courteeners-Phoebe-Fox-Club-NME-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Courteeners-Phoebe-Fox-Club-NME-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Courteeners-Phoebe-Fox-Club-NME-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Courteeners-Phoebe-Fox-Club-NME-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/courteeners">Courteeners</a> played the relaunch of Club NME with Ladbrokes Live this weekend (September 15) in London.</p><p> The Manchester band performed a career-spanning greatest hits set at London&#39;s EartH, followed by a surprise DJ guest set from <a href="/artists/the-libertines">The Libertines</a> &#39; Carl Barat and Gary Powell to close the evening alongside DJ Rowena.</p><p> Tickets were free to punters who queued around the street to guarantee entry, reintroducing the classic indie disco night that first launched in 2005 and became a staple of the club scene from London to Sao Paulo and beyond.</p><p> Taking to the stage for their first London show since March, Courteeners launched into cuts from 2013 album &#39;Anna&#39; including &#39;Are You In Love With A Notion?&#39; alongside classic &#39;St Jude&#39; hits like &#39;Cavorting&#39; and more.</p><p> The band played fan favourite &#39;Sycophant&#39; from 2010&#39;s &#39;Falcon&#39;, a song that frontman Liam Fray admitted he&#39;d not “sung that one for a long time”. A rowdy crowd that had travelled from across the country climbed on shoulders for &#39;The 17th&#39; from &#39;Mapping The Rendezvous&#39;, and &#39;St Jude&#39;s &#39;Not Nineteen Forever&#39; and &#39;What Took You So Long?&#39; </p><figure id="attachment_3499591" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3499591" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3499591" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Libertines-Club-NME-Phoebe-Fox.jpg" alt="The Libertines at Club NME" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Libertines-Club-NME-Phoebe-Fox.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Libertines-Club-NME-Phoebe-Fox-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Libertines-Club-NME-Phoebe-Fox-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Libertines-Club-NME-Phoebe-Fox-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Libertines-Club-NME-Phoebe-Fox-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/The-Libertines-Club-NME-Phoebe-Fox-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3499591" class="wp-caption-text"> The Libertines at Club NME. Credit: Phoebe Fox/NME</figcaption></figure><p> The Libertines&#39; Barat and Powell joined for a secret DJ set, which included mash-ups of The Killers and Gorillaz, alongside hits from Beastie Boys and more in a vibrant set.</p><p> Speaking to <i>NME</i> prior to the show, Courteeners&#39; Liam Fray commented on their upcoming music. “The new album has more songs than we need, so it&#39;s just a case of whittling it down now with some final touches. Hopefully end of year maybe we&#39;ll have something.”</p><p> Stay tuned to <em>NME</em> and <a class="c-link" href="http://ladbrokeslive.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-stringify-link="http://ladbrokeslive.co.uk" data-sk="tooltip_parent">ladbrokeslive.co.uk</a> for more coverage from the big night.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/courteeners-the-libertiens-club-nme-ladbrokes-live-3499586">Courteeners and The Libertines play rowdy relaunch of Club NME with Ladbrokes Live</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
